# Omninuera — Offer letter (Redlines & suggested edits)
[Company Address or Registered Office]

[Date]

[Candidate Name]
[Candidate Address]

Subject: Offer of Internship — AI Intern (3 months)

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera for the position of AI Intern on the terms set out below. ~~This offer is for an internship (stipend-based) and does not constitute an offer of regular employment.~~ **[Suggested replacement:]** This letter confirms a fixed‑term learning/training internship (the "Internship") and does not create an employer–employee relationship. The terms below set out the Internship arrangement; please read carefully.

1. Position and Duration
- Position: AI Intern.
- Duration: 3 months, commencing on [Start Date] and ending on the date three months thereafter unless extended in writing by Omninuera.
- **Training objectives (add):** The Internship is primarily for learning and training. Objectives include (i) exposure to data preprocessing, model experiments, documentation practices and (ii) supervised project work under [Reporting Manager]. The Company will provide a learning plan and periodic feedback.

2. Employment Type
- ~~Employment type: Internship (stipend-based), not regular employment. This engagement is on an internship basis only.~~
- **[Suggested replacement:]** Employment type: This engagement is a fixed‑term internship/training placement and is not intended to create an employer–employee relationship. You will not be eligible for employee benefits (such as Provident Fund, ESI, gratuity, paid leave) unless expressly stated in writing or required by applicable law. The stipend is a training allowance and not a salary.

3. Stipend
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month.
- Stipend payment terms: The stipend will be paid monthly via bank transfer to the bank account provided by you. **Payments are subject to applicable taxes and statutory deductions where required by law.** The Company will withhold taxes or other statutory contributions if and to the extent required by applicable law and will notify you of any such deductions.
- **[Add:]** You must provide PAN and bank account details and any required tax declarations (e.g., Form 15G/15H where applicable) prior to the first stipend payment. If you do not furnish PAN, TDS may be withheld at higher rates under law (Section 206AA, Income‑tax Act, 1961).

4. Location and Remote Work
- Location: Fully remote; the intern must be based in Bengaluru.
- Remote work and location-specific compliance: You will work remotely from your place of residence in Bengaluru. You must ensure compliance with any local regulations applicable to your place of residence. Omninuera may require documentation to confirm your Bengaluru residence for location-specific compliance purposes.
- **[Add:]** The Company may request proof of Bengaluru residency (e.g., local address proof) for compliance with local taxation or statutory requirements.

5. Reporting Line
- Reporting line: You will report to [Reporting Manager] (or such other person as may be designated by Omninuera).

6. Key Responsibilities
Your primary responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:
- Data preprocessing.
- Model experiments.
- Documentation.
- Collaboration with team members on assigned projects.
- **[Add:]** These responsibilities are part of supervised training; you are expected to follow the learning plan and participate in evaluations. The Company will not treat the Internship as a regular employment role.

7. Working Hours and Expectations
- Approximate weekly hours: Approximately 20–30 hours per week (flexible).
- Flexible schedule: Working hours are approximate and flexible; you are expected to coordinate with your Reporting Manager to agree on a schedule and meet project deadlines and deliverables.
- **[Add:]** Participation is expected but hours may vary for academic commitments (if you are a student). Please notify your Reporting Manager of any schedule conflicts.

8. Confidentiality and Non-Disclosure
- You will be required to maintain the confidentiality of Omninuera’s confidential information and trade secrets. ~~You will be required to sign Omninuera’s standard confidentiality and non-disclosure agreement (NDA) as a condition of beginning the internship.~~
- **[Suggested replacement/clarification:]** As a condition of this Internship you must sign the Company’s Internship Confidentiality and Invention Assignment Agreement (enclosed). The obligations will survive termination of the Internship in accordance with the confidentiality agreement.

9. Intellectual Property and Inventions
- ~~Intellectual Property: You agree that any inventions, discoveries, improvements, processes, designs, works of authorship, or other intellectual property conceived, developed, or reduced to practice by you, alone or with others, during the course of your internship and related to Omninuera’s business or using Omninuera resources, shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera. You agree to assign, and hereby assign, all right, title, and interest in such intellectual property to Omninuera and to execute any documents reasonably requested by Omninuera to perfect, confirm, or record Omninuera’s ownership.~~
- **[Suggested replacement (exact text to insert):]**
**Intellectual Property and Moral Rights**
a) You hereby assign to the Company, absolutely and exclusively, with full title guarantee, all present and future right, title and interest in any and all Intellectual Property (including inventions, improvements, designs, trademarks, copyrights, source code, computer programs, know‑how and documentation) created, conceived, developed or reduced to practice by you, alone or jointly, during the Internship period or arising from work performed for the Company (”Internship IP”).  
b) You agree to promptly disclose to the Company all such Internship IP and to execute all documents and do all acts necessary to enable the Company to obtain, perfect, register and enforce any rights in such Internship IP.  
c) To the extent permitted by law, you hereby waive or agree not to assert any moral rights in respect of the Internship IP and consent to any modifications, adaptations or uses of the Internship IP by the Company.  
d) This clause survives termination of the Internship.

10. Termination / Early Exit
- ~~Either party may terminate this internship with [notice period — see below] written notice. Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause, including breach of Omninuera policies, misconduct, unsatisfactory performance, or violation of confidentiality obligations.~~
- **[Suggested replacement (exact text to insert):]**
**Termination:** This Internship may be terminated by either party by giving seven (7) calendar days’ written notice to the other party. The Company may terminate the Internship with immediate effect for cause (including but not limited to misconduct, breach of confidentiality, or falsification of credentials). On termination you must return all Company property and confidential information. Termination ends the stipend obligation except for any stipend accrued but unpaid up to the date of termination.

11. Background Verification
- This offer is conditional upon successful completion of background verification checks, which may include identity, education, employment history, and other checks as required by Omninuera. Failure to satisfactorily complete background verification may result in withdrawal of this offer or termination of the internship.
- **[Add signed consent language (exact text to insert):]**
**Background Verification / Data Processing Consent:** You authorize the Company and its authorised third‑party agents to verify your education, employment history, criminal records, and other background information for recruitment and compliance purposes. You consent to the collection, processing and retention of personal data necessary for such checks and authorize third parties to provide such information to the Company. The purpose of processing is recruitment, background verification, training administration, and statutory compliance. The Company will retain this data for the period necessary for these purposes and will apply reasonable security practices as required under applicable law.

12. Benefits
- Benefits: No benefits are provided as part of this internship unless specifically stated in writing by Omninuera. Reimbursement policy: Any reimbursement for pre-approved, reasonable business expenses incurred in connection with your internship will be made in accordance with Omninuera’s expense reimbursement policy upon submission of valid receipts and approvals.
- **[Add:]** Travel or equipment reimbursements must be pre‑approved in writing. The Company may provide equipment on loan; title remains with the Company and must be returned on termination.

13. Taxes and Statutory Deductions
- The stipend will be subject to tax and statutory deductions as required by applicable law. You are responsible for providing accurate tax information and cooperating with Omninuera’s payroll team to facilitate proper withholding.
- **[Add guidance:]** If you are assessed as an employee for tax purposes, taxes will be withheld under Section 192 of the Income‑tax Act, 1961 and the Company will issue the appropriate certificate (Form 16). If the stipend is not subject to salary withholding, any non‑salary TDS (if applicable) will be handled under applicable provisions and Form 16A will be issued for TDS deducted. Please provide PAN to avoid higher withholding under Section 206AA.

14. Employee Policies and Code of Conduct
- You will be required to comply with Omninuera’s policies, procedures, and code of conduct during the internship, as provided to you.
- **[Add:]** For clarity, compliance with policies is a condition of the Internship, but compliance does not convert the Internship into employment.

15. Acceptance
To accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy of this letter to [HR Contact Name] at [HR Contact Email] by [Acceptance Deadline if any]. This offer is valid until such time as specified by Omninuera or until withdrawn.

Contact for acceptance and queries:
- Name: [HR Contact Name]
- Title: [HR Contact Title]
- Email: [HR Contact Email]
- Phone: [HR Contact Phone]

16. Miscellaneous
- Entire agreement: This letter constitutes the entire agreement between you and Omninuera regarding the internship engagement and supersedes all prior understandings.
- ~~Governing law: [Do not include jurisdictional/legal wording here; Legal to advise and insert appropriate clause.]~~
- **[Insert governing law clause (exact text):]** "This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. The parties irrevocably submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts at Bengaluru (Karnataka) for any dispute arising out of or in connection with this Agreement."

We look forward to you joining Omninuera as an AI Intern.

Sincerely,

For and on behalf of Omninuera

